    {
      "id": "PopularPost218799",
      "post_content": "It reads a lot better with the updated text: {T}: Return Coastal Wizard and another target creature to their owners' hands. Activate this ability only during your turn, before attackers are declared. This card is a good way of taking a nasty blocker (such as a Leviathan or a nasty [Wall of Frost](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wall of Frost) - [or Fire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=136284)) before swinging with something that wouldn't have the juice to jump said hurdle.\n  \n   \nIf Wizards was allowed to re-rule this card, I'd agree with Kurraga, except that I wouldn't give it Haste. On the other hand, if Haste *and* Flash were off the table, I think it shouldn't be limited to the owner's turn.\n  \nIn short:\n  \n{2}{U}{U} (1/1)\n  \n{T}: Return \"Coastal Wizard\" and another target creature to their owners' hands. Activate this ability before attackers are declared.\n  \n   \nThis would make CW a great means of removing a monstrous attacker **and** defender from play in the nick of time.\n  ",
      "posted_by": "Cybertronian",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost218799\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">It reads a lot better with the updated text: {T}: Return Coastal Wizard and another target creature to their owners' hands. Activate this ability only during your turn, before attackers are declared. This card is a good way of taking a nasty blocker (such as a Leviathan or a nasty <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wall of Frost\">Wall of Frost</a> - <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=136284\">or Fire</a>) before swinging with something that wouldn't have the juice to jump said hurdle.\r<br/> <br/>If Wizards was allowed to re-rule this card, I'd agree with Kurraga, except that I wouldn't give it Haste. On the other hand, if Haste <i>and</i> Flash were off the table, I think it shouldn't be limited to the owner's turn. \r<br/>In short:\r<br/>{2}{U}{U}  (1/1)\r<br/>{T}: Return \"Coastal Wizard\" and another target creature to their owners' hands. Activate this ability before attackers are declared.\r<br/> <br/>This would make CW a great means of removing a monstrous attacker <b>and</b> defender from play in the nick of time.\r<br/></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: <a class=\"postedByLink\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"PostedBy3000\">Cybertronian</a>\